 https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289442\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290308\n", "files": ["layout/generic/nsIFrame.cpp"], "git_node": "ccc711d72b7906abdfa03a9af8e848ef6ead9b02", "git_parents": ["153f00cfd0cf3d38d4a2de74da2ae229bc72e68d"], "node": "4c98e2d496a1d16ce2ebb622bcaae9846e934708", "parents": ["de169a66a06fce5d28d2eb819db378290794d5a0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774629970, "git_changesets": ["ccc711d72b7906abdfa03a9af8e848ef6ead9b02"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25234": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nika Layzell \u003cnika@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2020817 - Part 1: Clean up NetAddr ToString,  a=diannaS\n\nThis will be useful in later parts, as otherwise the changed callers would hit\nthe static analysis added in part 2. This new approach should also\ntheoretically be slightly more efficient in some cases.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D286155\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290170\n", "files": ["netwerk/base/ProxyAutoConfig.cpp", "netwerk/base/nsINetAddr.idl", "netwerk/base/nsNetAddr.cpp", "netwerk/base/nsSocketTransport2.cpp", "netwerk/dns/DNS.cpp", "netwerk/dns/DNS.h", "netwerk/dns/DNSPacket.cpp", "netwerk/dns/DNSRequestChild.cpp", "netwerk/dns/nsDNSService2.cpp", "netwerk/dns/nsHostRecord.cpp", "netwerk/dns/nsHostResolver.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/ConnectionEntry.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpBaseChannel.cpp", "netwerk/socket/nsSOCKSIOLayer.cpp", "netwerk/system/win32/nsNotifyAddrListener.cpp"], "git_node": "59a7428bd2c5fbbce8ba30e59c83d34ef95778b7", "git_parents": ["ccc711d72b7906abdfa03a9af8e848ef6ead9b02"], "node": "cf03fcd1e7ffb99b1ed8bceb6a9dab2bb2af221f", "parents": ["4c98e2d496a1d16ce2ebb622bcaae9846e934708"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nika Layzell \u003cnika@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2020817 - Part 2: Add a MOZ_NON_TERMINATED_STRING static analysis,  a=diannaS\n\nThis static analysis will identify and reject callers where folks are passing\nnsTStringRepr::BeginReading() or ::Data() to printf-style functions. These\nfunctions are not guaranteed to return a null terminated string, so should not\nbe used in these places.\n\nMost places which hit this analysis should not actually be security bugs, but\nwe should fix them anyways, as people will use them as examples of what to do\nand write bad code based off of them.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D286156\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290171\n", "files": ["build/clang-plugin/Checks.inc", "build/clang-plugin/ChecksIncludes.inc", "build/clang-plugin/CustomAttributes.inc", "build/clang-plugin/NonTerminatedStringChecker.cpp", "build/clang-plugin/NonTerminatedStringChecker.h", "build/clang-plugin/moz.build", "build/clang-plugin/tests/TestNonTerminatedString.cpp", "build/clang-plugin/tests/moz.build", "mfbt/Attributes.h"], "git_node": "b262190afdad4efd31ff0777052849511b20eba7", "git_parents": ["59a7428bd2c5fbbce8ba30e59c83d34ef95778b7"], "node": "c865a4148a6212726d3c5c865f93ef8c617a8709", "parents": ["cf03fcd1e7ffb99b1ed8bceb6a9dab2bb2af221f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nika Layzell \u003cnika@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2020817 - Part 3: Allow .get on nsTLiteralString,  a=diannaS\n\nThis was originally removed due to bug 1341513. Unfortunately this method can\nstill have occasional value in places which call use a macro which declares a\n`nsLiteral[C]String`. This changes some of those callers over & re-adds the\n`.get()`.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D286157\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290172\n", "files": ["layout/base/MobileViewportManager.cpp", "layout/base/ZoomConstraintsClient.cpp", "xpcom/string/nsTLiteralString.h"], "git_node": "09b083f10b4a7e5d2d6546134c60d264ccb5390b", "git_parents": ["b262190afdad4efd31ff0777052849511b20eba7"], "node": "bb06b4be01ce670a2bb27a84c31b8f401f8e4e2c", "parents": ["c865a4148a6212726d3c5c865f93ef8c617a8709"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nika Layzell \u003cnika@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2020817 - Part 4: Annotate & clean up nsACString callers of BeginReading/Data,  a=diannaS\n\nThis is a large number of largely mechanical changes. When possible, the code\nwas called to directly call `.get()` instead, performing the assertions\nmanually. In many places PromiseFlatCString() calls were added to dynamically\ncopy the strings into null terminated buffers if the string was not null\nterminated.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D286158\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290173\n", "files": ["browser/components/shell/nsWindowsShellService.cpp", "caps/BasePrincipal.cpp", "dom/base/nsContentPermissionHelper.cpp", "dom/cache/FileUtils.cpp", "dom/canvas/ClientWebGLContext.cpp", "dom/canvas/WebGL2Context.cpp", "dom/canvas/WebGL2ContextFramebuffers.cpp", "dom/canvas/WebGLContext.cpp", "dom/canvas/WebGLContext.h", "dom/canvas/WebGLContextDraw.cpp", "dom/canvas/WebGLContextUtils.cpp", "dom/canvas/WebGLContextVertices.cpp", "dom/canvas/WebGLFramebuffer.cpp", "dom/canvas/WebGLProgram.cpp", "dom/canvas/WebGLTextureUpload.cpp", "dom/canvas/WebGLValidateStrings.cpp", "dom/cookiestore/CookieStoreSubscriptionService.cpp", "dom/fetch/FetchChild.cpp", "dom/fetch/FetchService.cpp", "dom/indexedDB/ScriptErrorHelper.cpp", "dom/ipc/ProcessIsolation.cpp", "dom/media/MediaCache.cpp", "dom/media/MediaDecoder.cpp", "dom/media/doctor/DDLogValue.cpp", "dom/media/doctor/DDMediaLogs.cpp", "dom/media/doctor/DecoderDoctorDiagnostics.cpp", "dom/media/gmp/GMPDiskStorage.cpp", "dom/media/gmp/GMPMemoryStorage.cpp", "dom/media/gmp/GMPServiceParent.cpp", "dom/media/gmp/GMPStorageParent.cpp", "dom/media/gmp/GMPUtils.cpp", "dom/media/gtest/TestGMPUtils.cpp", "dom/media/gtest/TestVideoUtils.cpp", "dom/media/ipc/MFMediaEngineParent.cpp", "dom/media/mediaelement/HTMLMediaElement.cpp", "dom/media/mediasource/ContainerParser.cpp", "dom/media/mediasource/SourceBuffer.cpp", "dom/media/platforms/agnostic/AgnosticDecoderModule.cpp", "dom/media/platforms/android/AndroidDecoderModule.cpp", "dom/media/platforms/apple/AppleDecoderModule.cpp", "dom/media/platforms/ffmpeg/FFmpegDecoderModule.h", "dom/media/platforms/wmf/MFCDMSession.cpp", "dom/media/platforms/wmf/MFTEncoder.cpp", "dom/media/platforms/wmf/WMFDecoderModule.cpp", "dom/media/systemservices/MediaUtils.cpp", "dom/media/utils/PerformanceRecorder.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/MediaEngineRemoteVideoSource.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/MediaEngineWebRTCAudio.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/jsapi/MediaTransportHandler.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/jsapi/PeerConnectionImpl.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/transport/ipc/StunAddrsRequestParent.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/transport/ipc/WebrtcTCPSocket.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/transport/nr_socket_prsock.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/transport/test_nr_socket.cpp", "dom/media/webspeech/synth/nsSynthVoiceRegistry.cpp", "dom/navigation/Navigation.cpp", "dom/network/UDPSocket.cpp", "dom/network/UDPSocketParent.cpp", "dom/performance/Performance.cpp", "dom/quota/CheckedUnsafePtr.h", "dom/script/ScriptTrace.cpp", "dom/security/IntegrityPolicy.cpp", "dom/security/ResourceHasher.cpp", "dom/workers/RuntimeService.cpp", "dom/workers/WorkerError.cpp", "editor/spellchecker/EditorSpellCheck.cpp", "extensions/auth/nsAuthSambaNTLM.cpp", "extensions/auth/nsHttpNegotiateAuth.cpp", "extensions/permissions/PermissionManager.cpp", "gfx/gl/GLBlitHelper.cpp", "gfx/gl/GLContext.cpp", "gfx/gl/GLContext.h", "gfx/gl/SharedSurfaceD3D11Interop.cpp", "gfx/layers/opengl/CompositorOGL.cpp", "gfx/thebes/SharedFontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxDWriteFontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFT2FontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxUtils.cpp", "gfx/vr/ipc/VRChild.cpp", "gfx/vr/service/OpenVRSession.cpp", "gfx/webrender_bindings/WebRenderAPI.cpp", "image/ImageUtils.cpp", "ipc/glue/GeckoChildProcessHost.cpp", "js/xpconnect/loader/mozJSModuleLoader.cpp", "layout/base/nsLayoutDebugger.cpp", "layout/base/nsLayoutUtils.cpp", "modules/libjar/nsZipArchive.cpp", "modules/libpref/test/gtest/Basics.cpp", "netwerk/base/BackgroundFileSaver.cpp", "netwerk/base/nsNetUtil.cpp", "netwerk/base/nsPACMan.cpp", "netwerk/base/nsSocketTransport2.cpp", "netwerk/base/nsUDPSocket.cpp", "netwerk/cache2/CacheStorageService.cpp", "netwerk/cache2/Dictionary.cpp", "netwerk/cookie/CookieLogging.cpp", "netwerk/cookie/CookieParser.cpp", "netwerk/dns/GetAddrInfo.cpp", "netwerk/dns/TRRService.cpp", "netwerk/dns/nsHostResolver.cpp", "netwerk/mime/nsMIMEHeaderParamImpl.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/AlternateServices.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/ConnectionDiagnostics.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/Http2Compression.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/Http2Session.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/Http2StreamBase.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpConnectionUDP.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttp.h", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpAuthCache.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpBasicAuth.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpChannel.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpChannelAuthProvider.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnection.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnectionMgr.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpDigestAuth.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpTransaction.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsServerTiming.cpp", "netwerk/test/gtest/TestHttpResponseHead.cpp", "netwerk/test/gtest/TestPACMan.cpp", "netwerk/url-classifier/AsyncUrlChannelClassifier.cpp", "security/manager/ssl/CommonSocketControl.cpp", "security/manager/ssl/nsSecurityHeaderParser.cpp", "security/sandbox/common/test/SandboxTestingParent.cpp", "toolkit/components/aboutthirdparty/AboutThirdParty_TestMethods.cpp", "toolkit/components/backgroundtasks/BackgroundTasksRunner.cpp", "toolkit/components/contentanalysis/ContentAnalysis.cpp", "toolkit/components/cookiebanners/nsCookieInjector.cpp", "toolkit/components/glean/xpcom/FOG.cpp", "toolkit/components/reputationservice/ApplicationReputation.cpp", "toolkit/components/telemetry/core/Telemetry.cpp", "toolkit/components/telemetry/other/UntrustedModulesDataSerializer.cpp", "toolkit/components/terminator/nsTerminator.cpp", "toolkit/components/url-classifier/Classifier.cpp", "toolkit/components/url-classifier/nsUrlClassifierStreamUpdater.cpp", "toolkit/components/url-classifier/tests/gtest/TestURLsAndHashing.cpp", "toolkit/crashreporter/nsExceptionHandler.cpp", "toolkit/system/gnome/nsGIOService.cpp", "toolkit/system/windowsDHCPClient/tests/gtest/TestDHCPUtils.cpp", "toolkit/xre/nsXREDirProvider.cpp", "tools/profiler/core/platform.cpp", "tools/profiler/gecko/ProfilerChild.cpp", "tools/profiler/gecko/ProfilerParent.cpp", "tools/profiler/gecko/nsProfiler.cpp", "widget/GfxInfoBase.cpp", "widget/gtk/nsApplicationChooser.cpp", "widget/windows/GfxInfo.cpp", "widget/windows/JumpListBuilder.cpp", "widget/windows/WindowsTestDebug.cpp", "widget/windows/nsClipboard.cpp", "widget/windows/nsDataObj.cpp", "widget/windows/nsPrintSettingsWin.cpp", "widget/windows/nsPrinterWin.cpp", "widget/windows/nsWindowDbg.cpp", "widget/windows/nsWindowLoggedMessages.cpp", "xpcom/base/LogModulePrefWatcher.cpp", "xpcom/base/nsSystemInfo.cpp", "xpcom/build/perfprobe.cpp", "xpcom/ds/nsAtom.h", "xpcom/io/FileUtilsWin.h", "xpcom/io/nsLocalFileWin.cpp", "xpcom/string/nsTStringRepr.h", "xpcom/tests/gtest/TestBase64.cpp", "xpcom/tests/gtest/TestEscape.cpp", "xpcom/tests/gtest/TestMoveString.cpp", "xpcom/tests/gtest/TestUTF.cpp", "xpcom/tests/windows/TestNtPathToDosPath.cpp", "xpcom/threads/nsThread.cpp", "xpcom/threads/nsThreadUtils.cpp"], "git_node": "9798c5806cdae8939b80c949f645049e11e26795", "git_parents": ["09b083f10b4a7e5d2d6546134c60d264ccb5390b"], "node": "40f62ace168c3ee8726917a3299c5b8c84df4fb4", "parents": ["bb06b4be01ce670a2bb27a84c31b8f401f8e4e2c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774630382, "git_changesets": ["59a7428bd2c5fbbce8ba30e59c83d34ef95778b7", "b262190afdad4efd31ff0777052849511b20eba7", "09b083f10b4a7e5d2d6546134c60d264ccb5390b", "9798c5806cdae8939b80c949f645049e11e26795"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25235": {"changesets": [{"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024633: Put some IPC_FAIL calls back inside DEBUG ifdefs.  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nI was a bit overzealous in bug 2020542 (commit 0ae6880d5bf4).\nMy original intent there was to remove cases where we construct IPC_FAIL and then conditionally avoid returning it, since the mere construction of IPC_FAIL will be treated as a failure.\nHowever, I went a step further and constructed IPC_FAIL in cases where we previously didn't in release builds.\nWhile we shouldn't be hitting these, it turns out we do.\nFor now, put them back behind ifdef DEBUG to stop the bleeding.\nWe'll need to figure out why this is happening in a follow-up.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288818\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290300\n", "files": ["accessible/ipc/DocAccessibleParent.cpp"], "git_node": "c802d1852918d443beef2605a1980833fcef8641", "git_parents": ["9798c5806cdae8939b80c949f645049e11e26795"], "node": "16e71a34395cc7b514fccbde945dd574e5226698", "parents": ["40f62ace168c3ee8726917a3299c5b8c84df4fb4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774630782, "git_changesets": ["c802d1852918d443beef2605a1980833fcef8641"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25236": {"changesets": [{"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2017857 - Enforce prefs for dom TCP and UDP sockets  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287777\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290444\n", "files": ["dom/network/TCPSocket.cpp", "dom/network/TCPSocketParent.cpp", "dom/network/tests/chrome.toml", "ipc/glue/BackgroundParentImpl.cpp", "modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml", "netwerk/ipc/NeckoParent.cpp"], "git_node": "43f21c92942dd0bbcac1fb4a6a34c3e64ad64e41", "git_parents": ["c802d1852918d443beef2605a1980833fcef8641"], "node": "fa4b445c4938e3d52ec35266e1a6f5d6abe0b43b", "parents": ["16e71a34395cc7b514fccbde945dd574e5226698"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774630997, "git_changesets": ["43f21c92942dd0bbcac1fb4a6a34c3e64ad64e41"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25237": {"changesets": [{"author": "Bryan Johns \u003cbjohns@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2023716 - Load generic chat prompts for custom endpoints  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288095\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290496\n", "files": ["browser/components/aiwindow/models/Utils.sys.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/models/tests/xpcshell/ai-window-prompts-remote-settings-snapshot.json", "browser/components/aiwindow/models/tests/xpcshell/test_Utils_RemoteSettings.js"], "git_node": "73881032fa78d511101153666ec42f098c0468cf", "git_parents": ["43f21c92942dd0bbcac1fb4a6a34c3e64ad64e41"], "node": "40871266f4dfea90ad33ed852039f78c53fdb88e", "parents": ["fa4b445c4938e3d52ec35266e1a6f5d6abe0b43b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774631413, "git_changesets": ["73881032fa78d511101153666ec42f098c0468cf"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25238": {"changesets": [{"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024245 - make tickler threadsafe  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288861\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290455\n", "files": ["netwerk/base/Tickler.cpp", "netwerk/base/Tickler.h"], "git_node": "f3af7de85e4ed83a212d3e5523748e3d1a9b9100", "git_parents": ["73881032fa78d511101153666ec42f098c0468cf"], "node": "0445e58f57fa5ccb7e074775ce35c4373d00cb70", "parents": ["40871266f4dfea90ad33ed852039f78c53fdb88e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774632396, "git_changesets": ["f3af7de85e4ed83a212d3e5523748e3d1a9b9100"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25239": {"changesets": [{"author": "Randy Concepcion \u003crconcepcion@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2019693 - Persist securityProperties flags in SQLite chat storage  a=diannaS\n\nsecurityProperties on ChatConversation was set at runtime but not\npersisted to SQLite. When conversations were saved and restored, flags\nreset to defaults. Tainted conversations appeared clean after restore.\n\nAdds toJSON() and fromJSON() to SecurityProperties for serialization of\ncommitted flag state. ChatConversation constructor normalizes plain\nobjects from SQLite into SecurityProperties instances.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D285181\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290451\n", "files": ["browser/components/aiwindow/models/SecurityProperties.sys.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/modules/AIWindowConstants.sys.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/modules/ChatConversation.sys.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/modules/ChatMigrations.sys.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/modules/ChatSql.sys.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/modules/ChatStore.sys.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/modules/ChatUtils.sys.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/xpcshell/test_ChatConversation.js", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/xpcshell/test_ChatStore.js", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/xpcshell/test_chat-utils.js"], "git_node": "fb37094e96b0c75099d7b993f1d6b60343f23415", "git_parents": ["f3af7de85e4ed83a212d3e5523748e3d1a9b9100"], "node": "f9ec52e46b0889d41a2746a07f8f9fb282e7dd4e", "parents": ["0445e58f57fa5ccb7e074775ce35c4373d00cb70"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774632437, "git_changesets": ["fb37094e96b0c75099d7b993f1d6b60343f23415"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25240": {"changesets": [{"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2026426. Update libpng to v1.6.56.  a=diannaS\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290004\n", "files": ["media/libpng/ANNOUNCE", "media/libpng/AUTHORS", "media/libpng/CHANGES", "media/libpng/README", "media/libpng/arm/palette_neon_intrinsics.c", "media/libpng/libpng-manual.txt", "media/libpng/moz.yaml", "media/libpng/png.c", "media/libpng/png.h", "media/libpng/pngconf.h", "media/libpng/pngpriv.h", "media/libpng/pngread.c", "media/libpng/pngrtran.c", "media/libpng/pngrutil.c", "media/libpng/pngset.c", "media/libpng/pngstruct.h", "media/libpng/pngtrans.c", "media/libpng/pngwrite.c", "media/libpng/pngwutil.c"], "git_node": "53cc4f2877a561606f99d20aafc56e35a395f1e2", "git_parents": ["fb37094e96b0c75099d7b993f1d6b60343f23415"], "node": "01198f5b42a816666ac240f18c0c260e9779dfac", "parents": ["f9ec52e46b0889d41a2746a07f8f9fb282e7dd4e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774634908, "git_changesets": ["53cc4f2877a561606f99d20aafc56e35a395f1e2"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25241": {"changesets": [{"author": "Byron Campen \u003cdocfaraday@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2025520: Fix this comparison.  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289621\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290183\n", "files": ["dom/media/webrtc/transport/third_party/nICEr/src/stun/stun_proc.cpp"], "git_node": "e9f6f5f739eaf92a30c4ac2da3e2ebf0c56bda50", "git_parents": ["53cc4f2877a561606f99d20aafc56e35a395f1e2"], "node": "baf7f38508caa5228d29fecf6e755b8808123ce8", "parents": ["01198f5b42a816666ac240f18c0c260e9779dfac"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774635560, "git_changesets": ["e9f6f5f739eaf92a30c4ac2da3e2ebf0c56bda50"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25242": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jan-Ivar Bruaroey \u003cjib@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2025494 - Remove MOZ_UNANNOTATED.  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289885\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290191\n", "files": ["dom/media/webrtc/libwebrtcglue/WebrtcMediaDataEncoderCodec.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/libwebrtcglue/WebrtcMediaDataEncoderCodec.h"], "git_node": "b4868f10295d6c72c0c8f9ce2461678a80dd007f", "git_parents": ["e9f6f5f739eaf92a30c4ac2da3e2ebf0c56bda50"], "node": "7460fab57fb81bff8d839f5a85aac6d831e1bb4f", "parents": ["baf7f38508caa5228d29fecf6e755b8808123ce8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774635600, "git_changesets": ["b4868f10295d6c72c0c8f9ce2461678a80dd007f"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25243": {"changesets": [{"author": "Randell Jesup \u003crjesup@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024668: Minor fix for continuation in Activate()  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288715\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289527\n", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnection.cpp"], "git_node": "fc1f3b41b9f345af859d0acb887363f91fe0278a", "git_parents": ["b4868f10295d6c72c0c8f9ce2461678a80dd007f"], "node": "b0e0c55db164381b6547cce2c333db86832ee262", "parents": ["7460fab57fb81bff8d839f5a85aac6d831e1bb4f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774635642, "git_changesets": ["fc1f3b41b9f345af859d0acb887363f91fe0278a"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25244": {"changesets": [{"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024239 - Use specific IPC messages for flushing checkerboard reports.  a=diannaS\n\nThis limits the abilities of the GPU process more appropriately than\nthe previous approach which used a generic message that could\ndispatch any observer notification.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288592\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289910\n", "files": ["gfx/ipc/GPUChild.cpp", "gfx/ipc/GPUChild.h", "gfx/ipc/GPUParent.cpp", "gfx/ipc/GPUParent.h", "gfx/ipc/GPUProcessManager.cpp", "gfx/ipc/GPUProcessManager.h", "gfx/ipc/PGPU.ipdl", "gfx/layers/apz/src/APZCTreeManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/util/CheckerboardReportService.cpp"], "git_node": "d3825c88b093c207454a9b66b462fd8d812b35c3", "git_parents": ["fc1f3b41b9f345af859d0acb887363f91fe0278a"], "node": "6c036cd1d00c1e8b4867c6a441ec4e03602406c6", "parents": ["b0e0c55db164381b6547cce2c333db86832ee262"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774635683, "git_changesets": ["d3825c88b093c207454a9b66b462fd8d812b35c3"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25245": {"changesets": [{"author": "Brad Werth \u003cbwerth@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2023130: Remove variable shadow in RemoteTextureMap::WaitRemoteTextureReady.  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288061\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290509\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/RemoteTextureMap.cpp"], "git_node": "9a1be733f651dd9889f72ede035438f6b996457d", "git_parents": ["d3825c88b093c207454a9b66b462fd8d812b35c3"], "node": "29067225c6fd20a03094159744c8a575581a9132", "parents": ["6c036cd1d00c1e8b4867c6a441ec4e03602406c6"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774636578, "git_changesets": ["9a1be733f651dd9889f72ede035438f6b996457d"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25246": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kershaw Chang \u003ckershaw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024761 - WebSocketChannelChild cleanup,  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289497\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290139\n", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/websocket/WebSocketChannelChild.cpp"], "git_node": "4009ca457925447c93aa44ca114ed68122a05e33", "git_parents": ["9a1be733f651dd9889f72ede035438f6b996457d"], "node": "65f99e12c3b99db52acc048b7793873eb5aa15ec", "parents": ["29067225c6fd20a03094159744c8a575581a9132"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774637396, "git_changesets": ["4009ca457925447c93aa44ca114ed68122a05e33"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25247": {"changesets": [{"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2026289.  a=diannaS\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290314\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxUtils.cpp"], "git_node": "5d312ce8440362760c3c69c815d83732d2a385aa", "git_parents": ["4009ca457925447c93aa44ca114ed68122a05e33"], "node": "8ed0e329712072318e7d679ebce6a0b673497761", "parents": ["65f99e12c3b99db52acc048b7793873eb5aa15ec"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774637531, "git_changesets": ["5d312ce8440362760c3c69c815d83732d2a385aa"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25248": {"changesets": [{"author": "mimi \u003cnsauermann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024592 - Remove SMA CLICK_ELEMENT  a=diannaS\n\nNo messages referencing this SMA and there are no plans to and looks like the test coverage (`browser_sma_click_element.js`) was removed in [1869605](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1869605)\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288987\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290246\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/messaging-system/lib/SpecialMessageActions.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/messaging-system/schemas/SpecialMessageActionSchemas/SpecialMessageActionSchemas.json", "toolkit/components/messaging-system/schemas/SpecialMessageActionSchemas/index.md"], "git_node": "4f4776030d2efe611750fca9907e7fce23c8e7b0", "git_parents": ["5d312ce8440362760c3c69c815d83732d2a385aa"], "node": "4f4e0cb8ed1f52edbc7c0d9b6ce7915f32e7d4cb", "parents": ["8ed0e329712072318e7d679ebce6a0b673497761"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774638098, "git_changesets": ["4f4776030d2efe611750fca9907e7fce23c8e7b0"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25249": {"changesets": [{"author": "Brad Werth \u003cbwerth@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2023276 Part 1: Early exit DataSourceSurfaceFromYCbCrDescriptor when buffer is null.  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288733\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290502\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/ImageDataSerializer.cpp"], "git_node": "badbdd183ad00498f333f5d6eb1b8c201a38573c", "git_parents": ["4f4776030d2efe611750fca9907e7fce23c8e7b0"], "node": "8fe89678160e0be492cbecec85c8f2460af01e38", "parents": ["4f4e0cb8ed1f52edbc7c0d9b6ce7915f32e7d4cb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brad Werth \u003cbwerth@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2023276 Part 2: Early exit BufferTextureHost::GetAsSurface when buffer is null.  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288734\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290503\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/composite/TextureHost.cpp"], "git_node": "afebe91b6606e38d5af37e3375f9c1fe2a134880", "git_parents": ["badbdd183ad00498f333f5d6eb1b8c201a38573c"], "node": "a9f3d28b65d8e37d2673c0e30d63a01e15cae9e3", "parents": ["8fe89678160e0be492cbecec85c8f2460af01e38"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brad Werth \u003cbwerth@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2023276 Part 3: Early exit CreateBackendIndependentTextureHost for unreadable shmem.  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288735\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290504\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/composite/TextureHost.cpp"], "git_node": "01dc5d659107f66ea673aadec321bccb8cda3c4a", "git_parents": ["afebe91b6606e38d5af37e3375f9c1fe2a134880"], "node": "c117e03c869379a1fc8db5975420e01f67effe88", "parents": ["a9f3d28b65d8e37d2673c0e30d63a01e15cae9e3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774638184, "git_changesets": ["badbdd183ad00498f333f5d6eb1b8c201a38573c", "afebe91b6606e38d5af37e3375f9c1fe2a134880", "01dc5d659107f66ea673aadec321bccb8cda3c4a"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25250": {"changesets": [{"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2025746 - Middle clicking alternate engines should open a new tab in the background.  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289509\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290073\n", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/content/SmartbarInput.mjs", "browser/components/urlbar/content/UrlbarInput.mjs", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_searchModeSwitcher_basic.js"], "git_node": "0b51f27bc1af92872e379c85d20a4ebab7ea6929", "git_parents": ["01dc5d659107f66ea673aadec321bccb8cda3c4a"], "node": "ad9f3a46a579ed54f5d8f7da797fa2871e229f11", "parents": ["c117e03c869379a1fc8db5975420e01f67effe88"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774639948, "git_changesets": ["0b51f27bc1af92872e379c85d20a4ebab7ea6929"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25251": {"changesets": [{"author": "Teodor Tanasoaia \u003cttanasoaia@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2022554.  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288045\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289556\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxUtils.cpp"], "git_node": "9bdccd7cb6974d4d0c7de7ed4e633d0b9b2c5546", "git_parents": ["0b51f27bc1af92872e379c85d20a4ebab7ea6929"], "node": "11d2a4993faa0acd509023b779d1799c1dc3a310", "parents": ["ad9f3a46a579ed54f5d8f7da797fa2871e229f11"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774639994, "git_changesets": ["9bdccd7cb6974d4d0c7de7ed4e633d0b9b2c5546"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25252": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024981 - [devtools] Fix addProperty test helper. .  a=diannaS\n\nWe used to directly set the editor input value (via `input.value`), while the\nInplaceEditor was being initialized, which would mess up the initial autocomplete\nsuggestion code and prevent emiting some events the helper was relying on.\n\nThis patch updates the helper so it better matches what an actual interaction is,\nwaiting for the initial autocomplete suggestion to appear, and then typing the\nvalue in the field.\n\nA test needed to be updated as it was expecting the popup to be displayed after\nentering `color: red`, which doesn't actually show the popup (the value was updated\nso we do have the popup displayed).\nAnother test, in the changes panel, also had to be updated as the change in timing\nwas making an assertion to fail.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290181\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290488\n", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/changes/test/browser_changes_declaration_duplicate.js", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/test/browser_rules_add-property-cancel_02.js", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/test/head.js"], "git_node": "a7271d5b27b1f5b449d03a3803d691f0b38fb623", "git_parents": ["9bdccd7cb6974d4d0c7de7ed4e633d0b9b2c5546"], "node": "8a5ff50e03fc049ed1f114a2126717bfe00968d0", "parents": ["11d2a4993faa0acd509023b779d1799c1dc3a310"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774640076, "git_changesets": ["a7271d5b27b1f5b449d03a3803d691f0b38fb623"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25253": {"changesets": [{"author": "mandysGit \u003cmcheang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024078 - Add searchEngines.hasBeenUsed targeting attribute for Messaging System.  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nThis patch adds a new `searchEngines.hasBeenUsed` targeting attribute to the Messaging\nSystem. It exposes whether each app-provided config engine has been used (entered search mode).\n\nThis allows feature callouts to be conditioned on engine usage, so\nmessages can be limited once a user has already used a given search engine.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288301\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290229\n", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/components/asrouter/docs/targeting-attributes.md", "browser/components/asrouter/modules/ASRouterTargeting.sys.mjs", "browser/components/asrouter/tests/browser/browser_asrouter_targeting.js", "browser/components/urlbar/SearchModeSwitcher.sys.mjs", "browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarPrefs.sys.mjs", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser.toml", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_engine_used_on_search_mode.js", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_searchMode_perplexity.js"], "git_node": "2509a0a95399363428774c69e72797dd53e012db", "git_parents": ["a7271d5b27b1f5b449d03a3803d691f0b38fb623"], "node": "42621a5669447cf159054ca1615da6a7cf316eb2", "parents": ["8a5ff50e03fc049ed1f114a2126717bfe00968d0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774640149, "git_changesets": ["2509a0a95399363428774c69e72797dd53e012db"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25254": {"changesets": [{"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024250 - Always dispatch nsHttpChannel::Release to main thread  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288546\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290457\n", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpChannel.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpChannel.h"], "git_node": "f364560c201ea3ba8737cf3ca7ec3bdb87258a93", "git_parents": ["2509a0a95399363428774c69e72797dd53e012db"], "node": "1f73e790612f90fb4e867f0325b537be918f6ea8", "parents": ["42621a5669447cf159054ca1615da6a7cf316eb2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774640545, "git_changesets": ["f364560c201ea3ba8737cf3ca7ec3bdb87258a93"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25255": {"changesets": [{"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe.birchill@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2026287 - Add an isAlive check after a CompleteAsyncScroll call.  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289996\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290014\n", "files": ["layout/generic/ScrollContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": "a16826593cf0707b65a9cd7ed97f177e60425973", "git_parents": ["f364560c201ea3ba8737cf3ca7ec3bdb87258a93"], "node": "c7975c