 "158daa2273be84ff27568f11cf4b3138e9d2356f", "parents": ["82dad77589c54ace77cff443fbd9adafa97f77bf"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774923777, "git_changesets": ["c638c160d8d7586b9405187ed04d199ebdfc209b"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25358": {"changesets": [{"author": "Eitan Isaacson \u003ceitan@monotonous.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2022225 - Don't unbind the child in RecvBindChildDoc.  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nIt should never be bound to a parent doc. If it is, we should fail just\nas we do in AddChildDoc when the child doc has a parent.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287196\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291069\n", "files": ["accessible/ipc/DocAccessibleParent.cpp"], "git_node": "d3934cb0f1c4db10a324ea22a1abab1af364fe44", "git_parents": ["c638c160d8d7586b9405187ed04d199ebdfc209b"], "node": "6e2a6752341fd115cb066b5d6288cea7d8c6b225", "parents": ["158daa2273be84ff27568f11cf4b3138e9d2356f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774923823, "git_changesets": ["d3934cb0f1c4db10a324ea22a1abab1af364fe44"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25359": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kershaw Chang \u003ckershaw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024468 - Ensure UDPSocket remains alive during CloseWithReason,  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290384\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290992\n", "files": ["dom/network/UDPSocket.cpp"], "git_node": "f27c98168a2f06a71131a41eead85e660cbf4007", "git_parents": ["d3934cb0f1c4db10a324ea22a1abab1af364fe44"], "node": "82f2ab25982113edb8bf773044af546a230b0b45", "parents": ["6e2a6752341fd115cb066b5d6288cea7d8c6b225"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774924483, "git_changesets": ["f27c98168a2f06a71131a41eead85e660cbf4007"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25360": {"changesets": [{"author": "Randell Jesup \u003crjesup@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2022041: Add IsSocketClosed()  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288306\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290681\n", "files": ["dom/network/UDPSocketParent.cpp", "netwerk/base/nsUDPSocket.cpp", "netwerk/base/nsUDPSocket.h"], "git_node": "652e0002618877b55e6b6e4ed410b11cea714949", "git_parents": ["f27c98168a2f06a71131a41eead85e660cbf4007"], "node": "5aac797e9343d6f47e6ca7bb29896681c6d04e07", "parents": ["82f2ab25982113edb8bf773044af546a230b0b45"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774924525, "git_changesets": ["652e0002618877b55e6b6e4ed410b11cea714949"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25361": {"changesets": [{"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1912015 - Use proxy method for some JNI methods in LayerViewSupport. .  a=diannaS\n\n`LayerViewSupport` has a race condition by disposing this object and\ncalling JNI methods. According to the crash reports, `onBoundsChanged`\nand `onSafeAreaChanged` are possible called after `LayerViewSupport` is\ndisposed. In other word, some methods that notify Gecko of changing\nwindow size etc by `onGlobalLayout` or `onApplyWindowInsets`) might be\ncalled after window is being destroyed.\n\nSo we should use proxy method and `WindowEvent` class to avoid it.\n`WindowEvent` will check if the object is attached during\n`Runnable::Run`.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289083\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291087\n", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoSession.java", "widget/android/jni/Natives.h", "widget/android/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": "af72e050c1c9a9c66c7230ee0eb8728c9eae0a9c", "git_parents": ["652e0002618877b55e6b6e4ed410b11cea714949"], "node": "7a94edb539957d7da9874dcd58ff2543c034cbc8", "parents": ["5aac797e9343d6f47e6ca7bb29896681c6d04e07"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774924743, "git_changesets": ["af72e050c1c9a9c66c7230ee0eb8728c9eae0a9c"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25362": {"changesets": [{"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2022252.  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287308\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290034\n", "files": ["image/decoders/nsBMPDecoder.cpp", "image/decoders/nsBMPDecoder.h", "image/decoders/nsICODecoder.cpp"], "git_node": "8a96e1ab15103ab44a3b86091f5bdbe83053980f", "git_parents": ["af72e050c1c9a9c66c7230ee0eb8728c9eae0a9c"], "node": "0ad1d756b959a65a70090f6408cf9670f135148f", "parents": ["7a94edb539957d7da9874dcd58ff2543c034cbc8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774925631, "git_changesets": ["8a96e1ab15103ab44a3b86091f5bdbe83053980f"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25363": {"changesets": [{"author": "Simon Farre \u003csimon.farre.cx@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024433 - Notify of attribute change in BlastSubtree  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nBlastSubtreeToPieces is called during error recovery. It makes sense to\nnotify of attribute changes.\n\nThis effectively means extra work during error recovery, but the\nreasoning is that this should happen (very) rarely and when it does,\nit's fine to do the \"extra\" work.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289225\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290512\n", "files": ["dom/base/Document.cpp"], "git_node": "a5d6605ab67accd756ea72fdf204a4c65154089a", "git_parents": ["8a96e1ab15103ab44a3b86091f5bdbe83053980f"], "node": "025b7393461e4c53dbb8661da031826fe7e2b89a", "parents": ["0ad1d756b959a65a70090f6408cf9670f135148f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774925672, "git_changesets": ["a5d6605ab67accd756ea72fdf204a4c65154089a"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25364": {"changesets": [{"author": "Byron Campen \u003cdocfaraday@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024458: Hold a self-ref on behalf of sigslot, just in ca