", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2021290 - [devtools] Skip browser_toolbox_split_console.js on linux debug r=bomsy,devtools-reviewers, a=test-only DONTBUILD\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289722\n", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/test/browser.toml"], "git_node": "3dea6fd4d5e814aa65810fdf271377b5bb7c586a", "git_parents": ["800ae5c45aa6cbbcbe460d38eb75d4e79caab492"], "node": "c652d94e74fe248a27b8bbb6f64795d02a15ebe1", "parents": ["d0ae798f18bb8fc89167acf6063fe65b76b90a8e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774968751, "git_changesets": ["3dea6fd4d5e814aa65810fdf271377b5bb7c586a"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25377": {"changesets": [{"author": "longsonr \u003clongsonr@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024463 - Part 1 Check list size  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289110\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290659\n", "files": ["dom/svg/DOMSVGLengthList.cpp", "dom/svg/DOMSVGNumberList.cpp", "dom/svg/DOMSVGPointList.cpp", "dom/svg/DOMSVGTransformList.cpp"], "git_node": "9f98662f9d6142a3a47c5e5bebaa35de1b37c0ac", "git_parents": ["3dea6fd4d5e814aa65810fdf271377b5bb7c586a"], "node": "ec5708ca9e9cd634df1dc4ea9628a37784edf9d9", "parents": ["c652d94e74fe248a27b8bbb6f64795d02a15ebe1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "longsonr \u003clongsonr@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024463 - Part 2 Add more asserts  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289188\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290660\n", "files": ["dom/svg/DOMSVGLength.cpp", "dom/svg/DOMSVGLength.h", "dom/svg/DOMSVGNumber.h", "dom/svg/DOMSVGPoint.cpp", "dom/svg/DOMSVGPoint.h", "dom/svg/DOMSVGTransform.h"], "git_node": "446ffe596053015adfa02b42b632040a8582532a", "git_parents": ["9f98662f9d6142a3a47c5e5bebaa35de1b37c0ac"], "node": "a1487a7a70c83a6ede7b6437ab4b76b7596a0c81", "parents": ["ec5708ca9e9cd634df1dc4ea9628a37784edf9d9"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774969277, "git_changesets": ["9f98662f9d6142a3a47c5e5bebaa35de1b37c0ac", "446ffe596053015adfa02b42b632040a8582532a"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25378": {"changesets": [{"author": "Edgar Chen \u003cechen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024553 \u2013 Emit a warning instead of asserting on out-of-order keydown and keypress events;  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290489\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291052\n", "files": ["dom/ipc/BrowserChild.cpp"], "git_node": "bdc333003c237be5af5e4a94c50e8de1a166fa6c", "git_parents": ["446ffe596053015adfa02b42b632040a8582532a"], "node": "d42d1192ff7d348e0b613f51a0381212cef85726", "parents": ["a1487a7a70c83a6ede7b6437ab4b76b7596a0c81"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774973243, "git_changesets": ["bdc333003c237be5af5e4a94c50e8de1a166fa6c"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25379": {"changesets": [{"author": "Bob Owen \u003cbobowencode@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2023094 p1 - Trigger AppLocker checks for CDM DLLs before lowering the sandbox.  a=diannaS\n\nPublisher AppLocker rules are currently blocked by the sandbox. Without\nexecuting any code from the DLL, we trigger the check before lowering the\nsandbox. A successful check is cached and then succeeds within the sandbox.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287544\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291215\n", "files": ["dom/media/gmp/GMPLoader.cpp", "xpcom/base/nsWindowsHelpers.h"], "git_node": "f0cc29a1e26ece6593da2fbd94803972f5c5d30c", "git_parents": ["bdc333003c237be5af5e4a94c50e8de1a166fa6c"], "node": "704ddf063e30e18c7cbbbbead9ce68b8fd1d419e", "parents": ["d42d1192ff7d348e0b613f51a0381212cef85726"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bob Owen \u003cbobowencode@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2023094 p2 - Update AppLocker sandbox rules.  a=diannaS\n\nThis makes two changes:\n1) Remove an old rule which allowed for a double slash in the registry path.\n   This was seen in a log when these rules were originally added, it cannot now\n   be found in any of the DLLs analyzed from Windows 7 onwards.\n2) A new rule to allow read access to System32\\AppLocker\\MDM. This folder is\n   required as part of checks to see if an AppLocker policy is configured.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D287545\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291216\n", "files": ["security/sandbox/win/src/sandboxbroker/sandboxBroker.cpp"], "git_node": "16c3f3bcd3dccde145b9d133dbad601bfc1c255f", "git_parents": ["f0cc29a1e26ece6593da2fbd94803972f5c5d30c"], "node": "37a58145085ff420682ed86e1686c50572ed22b4", "parents": ["704ddf063e30e18c7cbbbbead9ce68b8fd1d419e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774973514, "git_changesets": ["f0cc29a1e26ece6593da2fbd94803972f5c5d30c", "16c3f3bcd3dccde145b9d133dbad601bfc1c255f"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25380": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2027455 - Disable WebGL if GPU process disabled on platforms with a GPU process.  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289934\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290943\n", "files": ["dom/canvas/ClientWebGLContext.cpp", "gfx/config/gfxFeature.h", "gfx/config/gfxVars.h", "gfx/ipc/CanvasManagerParent.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxPlatform.cpp", "modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml", "testing/profiles/base/user.js", "widget/GfxInfoBase.cpp", "widget/GfxInfoFeatureDefs.inc"], "git_node": "ecaf454f56d59ac2feb1696b67fd7322c16dca30", "git_parents": ["16c3f3bcd3dccde145b9d133dbad601bfc1c255f"], "node": "7bf6a54a2edd78f00da460cd2686a8d6c28a7beb", "parents": ["37a58145085ff420682ed86e1686c50572ed22b4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774974632, "git_changesets": ["ecaf454f56d59ac2feb1696b67fd7322c16dca30"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25381": {"changesets": [{"author": "Artur Iunusov \u003caiunusov@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2019004 - FIX Double-Close Race in FileSystemAccessHandle via Dual IPC Channels,  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D286192\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291212\n", "files": ["dom/fs/parent/FileSystemAccessHandle.cpp"], "git_node": "f03db0cc4b5d7b8113adbc993bcc35108264b4f4", "git_parents": ["ecaf454f56d59ac2feb1696b67fd7322c16dca30"], "node": "51d5244a858825e772a3cfc37100d07983161710", "parents": ["7bf6a54a2edd78f00da460cd2686a8d6c28a7beb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774976368, "git_changesets": ["f03db0cc4b5d7b8113adbc993bcc35108264b4f4"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25382": {"changesets": [{"author": "Henri Sivonen \u003chsivonen@hsivonen.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024417.  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289170\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290810\n", "files": ["dom/base/nsGlobalWindowInner.cpp", "dom/base/nsPIDOMWindow.h", "dom/clients/manager/ClientSource.cpp"], "git_node": "890b22835b3118cb44161723a7e60b54f20f2571", "git_parents": ["f03db0cc4b5d7b8113adbc993bcc35108264b4f4"], "node": "96196e174ba8f12f156e4d1d46e65f4514a890e7", "parents": ["51d5244a858825e772a3cfc37100d07983161710"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774976410, "git_changesets": ["890b22835b3118cb44161723a7e60b54f20f2571"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25383": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jeff Muizelaar \u003cjmuizelaar@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2026306 - Fix reporting in ShaderValidatorResults::SizeOfIncludingThis.  a=diannaS\n\nThis avoids reporting interior pointers for the vectors.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289869\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291227\n", "files": ["dom/canvas/WebGLShaderValidator.cpp"], "git_node": "b2fd0978ca2329883bad8fa5fcbeb40d6cabc367", "git_parents": ["890b22835b3118cb44161723a7e60b54f20f2571"], "node": "bebf07549611029069643cc08c4d97599015070b", "parents": ["96196e174ba8f12f156e4d1d46e65f4514a890e7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774976452, "git_changesets": ["b2fd0978ca2329883bad8fa5fcbeb40d6cabc367"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25384": {"changesets": [{"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2027302.  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290770\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291269\n", "files": ["dom/canvas/DrawTargetWebgl.cpp"], "git_node": "5079356b582c4a39b6fa06c7bd8bafed23c6d158", "git_parents": ["b2fd0978ca2329883bad8fa5fcbeb40d6cabc367"], "node": "4d31992a92b29482fabe6b8763f6f17d7c317343", "parents": ["bebf07549611029069643cc08c4d97599015070b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774978348, "git_changesets": ["5079356b582c4a39b6fa06c7bd8bafed23c6d158"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25385": {"changesets": [{"author": "Florian Zia \u003cfzia@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2009615 - Part 1: Add telemetry extra_key location for smartbar engagement telemetry  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288013\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291295\n", "files": ["browser/components/aiwindow/metrics.yaml", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/components/ai-window/ai-window.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/browser.toml", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/browser_aiwindow_smartbar_telemetry.js", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/browser_smartwindow_telemetry.js", "browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarController.sys.mjs", "browser/components/urlbar/content/SmartbarInput.mjs", "browser/components/urlbar/metrics.yaml"], "git_node": "7f637c12a64e313ca6fc391b48fa7f4905894ae9", "git_parents": ["5079356b582c4a39b6fa06c7bd8bafed23c6d158"], "node": "5f1412452020f1e72640d947b3d166e22c0cd21d", "parents": ["4d31992a92b29482fabe6b8763f6f17d7c317343"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Zia \u003cfzia@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2009615 - Part 2: Add telemetry for smartbar input, intent and mentions  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288855\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291296\n", "files": ["browser/components/aiwindow/metrics.yaml", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/components/ai-website-chip/ai-website-chip.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/components/ai-window/ai-window.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/browser.toml", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/browser_aiwindow_smartbar_mentions.js", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/browser_aiwindow_smartbar_telemetry.js", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/head.js", "browser/components/urlbar/content/SmartbarInput.mjs", "browser/components/urlbar/content/SmartbarInputUtils.mjs", "tools/@types/generated/lib.gecko.dom.d.ts", "tools/@types/generated/lib.gecko.glean.d.ts", "tools/@types/generated/lib.gecko.xpcom.d.ts"], "git_node": "1f65ee98fd32747545cb3f46c7e33cd0a5803255", "git_parents": ["7f637c12a64e313ca6fc391b48fa7f4905894ae9"], "node": "c85b173237d692cf813c9d38c45a4abae37fb374", "parents": ["5f1412452020f1e72640d947b3d166e22c0cd21d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Zia \u003cfzia@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2009615 - Part 3: Add extra_keys to Smartbar suggestions telemetry  a=diannaS\n\nAdds the extra_keys chat_id, intent and model to the urlbar telemetry when SAP is smartbar.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289226\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291000\n", "files": ["browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/browser_aiwindow_smartbar_telemetry.js", "browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarController.sys.mjs", "browser/components/urlbar/content/SmartbarInput.mjs", "browser/components/urlbar/metrics.yaml", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/engagementTelemetry/browser/browser_glean_telemetry_engagement_sap.js"], "git_node": "84a788e9dd13935c6b3340ab665337f6e6da5e93", "git_parents": ["1f65ee98fd32747545cb3f46c7e33cd0a5803255"], "node": "cb1e3caf17519b2602fb407755cf469d778a58a0", "parents": ["c85b173237d692cf813c9d38c45a4abae37fb374"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774981301, "git_changesets": ["7f637c12a64e313ca6fc391b48fa7f4905894ae9", "1f65ee98fd32747545cb3f46c7e33cd0a5803255", "84a788e9dd13935c6b3340ab665337f6e6da5e93"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25386": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Schuster \u003ctschuster@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2025354  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289817\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291200\n", "files": ["docshell/base/BrowsingContext.cpp", "docshell/base/BrowsingContext.h", "js/xpconnect/src/XPCJSRuntime.cpp"], "git_node": "00a31fe2bb1720ecc8e63dc5734124795337407b", "git_parents": ["84a788e9dd13935c6b3340ab665337f6e6da5e93"], "node": "edff7313456f1228f049a526360eceb386e924cc", "parents": ["cb1e3caf17519b2602fb407755cf469d778a58a0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774983912, "git_changesets": ["00a31fe2bb1720ecc8e63dc5734124795337407b"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25387": {"changesets": [{"author": "Giulia Cardieri \u003cgcardieri@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2025589: Send descriptive string on error for modelResponse telemetry  a=diannaS\n\nGoal: send a string describing the type of error instead of the error code. For generic error, we don't have more information to send.\n\nAPI documentation for the error codes: https://firefox-ai.github.io/MLPA/#tag/LiteLLM/operation/chat_completion_v1_chat_completions_post\n\nBased on this Slack thread: https://mozilla.slack.com/archives/C0A163P9N2K/p1773989765337409\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289672\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291038\n", "files": ["browser/components/aiwindow/ui/components/ai-window/ai-window.mjs", "browser/components/aiwindow/ui/test/browser/browser_smartwindow_request_response_telemetry.js"], "git_node": "297827132187bc82045c2d67eac75b2b7d3a76c3", "git_parents": ["00a31fe2bb1720ecc8e63dc5734124795337407b"], "node": "801bcff4c2fea52103a7aa7d34fdfd60e73f308f", "parents": ["edff7313456f1228f049a526360eceb386e924cc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774983974, "git_changesets": ["297827132187bc82045c2d67eac75b2b7d3a76c3"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25388": {"changesets": [{"author": "Rebecca King \u003crking@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2026804 - Disable Turn on VPN button for Connecting state -  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290566\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291195\n", "files": ["browser/components/ipprotection/content/ipprotection-status-card.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser_IPProtectionService.js", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser_ipprotection_status_card.js"], "git_node": "f389e77f15472d6683a7a7275614746851e7edf8", "git_parents": ["297827132187bc82045c2d67eac75b2b7d3a76c3"], "node": "26ac94f7412f13355d15dc70b604b418c8946377", "parents": ["801bcff4c2fea52103a7aa7d34fdfd60e73f308f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774984262, "git_changesets": ["f389e77f15472d6683a7a7275614746851e7edf8"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25389": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2015952 - patch 1 - Clean up some variable declarations and redundant #includes in thebes font code.  a=diannaS\n\n(No behavior change, this is just some preparatory cleanup.)\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288945\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290091\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxFont.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFontEntry.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFontEntry.h", "layout/style/ServoStyleSet.cpp"], "git_node": "be5b7601d13f5445f5728683a72f17e4a3fe1651", "git_parents": ["f389e77f15472d6683a7a7275614746851e7edf8"], "node": "bc01e64848cbde6558ff983471631c6813864e3d", "parents": ["26ac94f7412f13355d15dc70b604b418c8946377"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2015952 - patch 2 - Try to bypass font table cache in gfxFontconfigFontEntry.  a=diannaS\n\nIf the FcPattern includes the pathname of the font file, we can use\nhb_face_create_from_file_or_fail to create an hb_face that directly\naccesses the memory-mapped file, rather than going through our GetFontTable\ncallback that relies on FreeType table access and the font table cache.\n\nThis means that such fonts will entirely bypass the table cache with its\ntricky management of blob ownership/lifetimes.\n\nThe old code is left in place as a fallback path for fonts where\nhb_face_create_from_file_or_fail fails. This should normally be limited\nto non-sfnt fonts such as legacy Type 1 resources, which are still found\non some Linux systems although they don't support modern font features.\nSuch fonts will still go via the table cache, etc. (although the tables\nbeing cached will be empty), but usage of it will be greatly reduced.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288946\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290092\n", "files": ["gfx/2d/2D.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxFontEntry.h"], "git_node": "9f6685b7499689338507b4420daff9c4def912a6", "git_parents": ["be5b7601d13f5445f5728683a72f17e4a3fe1651"], "node": "ccc8a3fd0fcd98cc3a7c1ad410e6f5b4edd2a5e0", "parents": ["bc01e64848cbde6558ff983471631c6813864e3d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2015952 - patch 3 - Simplify FontTableCache to avoid potential race.  a=diannaS\n\n(Based on Emilio's earlier patch here)\n\nThis simplifies the FontTableCache to avoid the weak-referencing scheme;\nnow once a table is cached, it will be retained indefinitely. Since most\nfonts bypass the cache, and non-sfnt fonts that still use it will have\nnull \"tables\", the memory footprint should be minimal.\n\nIn addition, the cache is removed entirely from gfxFontEntry on platforms\nthat don't use it, and only created if needed.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288947\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290093\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/CoreTextFontList.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxDWriteFontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxDWriteFontList.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxFT2FontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFT2FontList.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxFontEntry.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFontEntry.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxUserFontSet.h"], "git_node": "531361019957d80387034ea82be3af06e6cd1cdf", "git_parents": ["9f6685b7499689338507b4420daff9c4def912a6"], "node": "3785efef1a6e4b8cc5211b9cefa87d8cfad5d5d8", "parents": ["ccc8a3fd0fcd98cc3a7c1ad410e6f5b4edd2a5e0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2015952 - patch 4 - Cache hb-face in FT2FontEntry if it wraps a disk file.  a=diannaS\n\nLike in the fontconfig backend, on Android we can also use\nhb_face_create_from_file_or_fail to efficiently create an hb_face\nfor installed fonts that are available as disk resources.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288951\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290094\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxFT2FontList.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFT2FontList.h"], "git_node": "4db1e85bbeec3cfe39c538d8ed678fafe3fa8858", "git_parents": ["531361019957d80387034ea82be3af06e6cd1cdf"], "node": "aae513671d3bd7f55816bfc5ea6e5bc986a18aef", "parents": ["3785efef1a6e4b8cc5211b9cefa87d8cfad5d5d8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2026947 - Configure harfbuzz properly for mmap() support.  a=diannaS\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290534\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290704\n", "files": ["gfx/harfbuzz/src/moz.build"], "git_node": "ec2fd1acb886fd6600d38814849599701addbafc", "git_parents": ["4db1e85bbeec3cfe39c538d8ed678fafe3fa8858"], "node": "370b54a83dad367a7ac5b895d6ef5963d86debe0", "parents": ["aae513671d3bd7f55816bfc5ea6e5bc986a18aef"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774984340, "git_changesets": ["be5b7601d13f5445f5728683a72f17e4a3fe1651", "9f6685b7499689338507b4420daff9c4def912a6", "531361019957d80387034ea82be3af06e6cd1cdf", "4db1e85bbeec3cfe39c538d8ed678fafe3fa8858", "ec2fd1acb886fd6600d38814849599701addbafc"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25390": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan Hunt \u003crhunt@eqrion.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2024918 - Fix scalar replacement.  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D288998\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291257\n", "files": ["js/src/jit/ScalarReplacement.cpp"], "git_node": "79331863ae4691e2a2457b0d110e900cd9430665", "git_parents": ["ec2fd1acb886fd6600d38814849599701addbafc"], "node": "1f77dfc560d18b26a1bd24b8946913c6ba9af254", "parents": ["370b54a83dad367a7ac5b895d6ef5963d86debe0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1774985512, "git_changesets": ["79331863ae4691e2a2457b0d110e900cd9430665"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25391": {"changesets": [{"author": "Henri Sivonen \u003chsivonen@hsivonen.fi\u003e", "br