es.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289880\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D292797\n", "files": ["dom/animation/ScrollTimeline.h", "dom/animation/ViewTimeline.h", "layout/style/TimelineManager.cpp", "layout/style/crashtests/2024017.html", "layout/style/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": "8df6e39ba18c1992a51796a2af670b977c72238b", "git_parents": ["23e4eb43dea4819595a4a71f142a4a55140cbbb5"], "node": "b341bf0ba3adfc54c62eb0dafe88db57d8db19d7", "parents": ["63df2ce4d3f3a579fe3a8702911f2c566ebd358c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1775665487, "git_changesets": ["8df6e39ba18c1992a51796a2af670b977c72238b"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "25595": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2025962 - Add back pointer to queued CleanupRunnable  a=RyanVM DONTBUILD\n\nCurrently this checks whether it needs to dispatch a runnable based on whether\nthere are already callbacks in mCallbacks, but it can just as easily keep a\nweak pointer to any dispatched runnable and that lets us signal to the runnable\nthat there's nothting to do when FinalizationRegistryCleanup is destroyed.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D289786\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D292776\n", "files": ["xpcom/base/CycleCollectedJSContext.cpp", "xpcom/base/CycleCollectedJSContext.h"], "git_node": "9621dcf8822883f637ec94f2d197d7a10ed70444", "git_parents": ["8df6e39ba18c1992a51796a2af670b977c72238b"], "node": "0dda227072dfdc5d065085198a8a8c387fe5aba0", "parents": ["b341bf0ba3adfc54c62eb0dafe88db57d8db19d7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1775665534, "git_changesets": ["9621dcf8822883f637ec94f2d197d7a10ed70444"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "25596": {"changesets": [{"author": "Randell Jesup \u003crjesup@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2025489: avoid overflows  a=RyanVM DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal