or.services.mozilla.com/D288964\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D292679\n", "files": ["dom/fs/child/FileSystemRequestHandler.cpp", "dom/fs/include/fs/FileSystemRequestHandler.h", "dom/fs/test/gtest/FileSystemMocks.h"], "git_node": "f2827b15846e9022c31ef178be9e6c76b98b0d3d", "git_parents": ["1026cc399c92562270b16a37dd75ea2f6bc6d417"], "node": "9d27b66972641ef3bfab67b37468a3f0eb251130", "parents": ["b621e262df4641fbbc802fd65f1abe254d841b49"], "tags": []}], "date": 1775669780, "git_changesets": ["f2827b15846e9022c31ef178be9e6c76b98b0d3d"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "25602": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2029316 - Use setElement in UnmappedArgSetter to check if the argument was marked as deleted.  a=RyanVM DONTBUILD\n\nThis is more consistent with `UnmappedArgGetter` and better handles the case where\nthe property was marked deleted in `RareArgumentsData` but not actually deleted from\nthe object due to OOM. Unfortunately this scenario is hard to prevent because the property\nis marked as deleted in the `ArgumentsObject::obj_delProperty` class hook and after that\n`NativeDeleteProperty` tries to remove the property and this can fail.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D292409\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D292694\n", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/arguments/bug2029316.js", "js/src/vm/ArgumentsObject.cpp"], "git_node": "62590f9acafb86fc0cc9928abc13e49299b10c08", "git_parents": ["f2827b15846e9022c31ef178be9e6c76b98b0d3d"], "node": "09c4f64544270ed84850fd4f9f948694445c1df3", "parents": ["9d27b66972641ef3bfab67b37468a3f0eb251130"], "tags": []}], "date": 1775669826, "git_changesets": ["62590f9acafb86fc0cc9928abc13e49299b10c08"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "25603": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2029317 - Create RareArgumentsData before mutating the arguments object in MappedArgumentsObject::obj_defineProperty.  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D292408\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D292692\n", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/arguments/bug2029317.js", "js/src/vm/ArgumentsObject.cpp"], "git_node": "3e32101fc294b8a3fc881fce84a1e9a1b385b84b", "git_parents": ["62590f9acafb86fc0cc9928abc13e49299b10c08"], "node": "b55b7a4a82b568cc2756db0a696cc80e45d60cca", "parents": ["09c4f64544270ed84850fd4f9f948694445c1df3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1775669871, "git_changesets": ["3e32101fc294b8a3fc881fce84a1e9a1b385b84b"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "25604": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mugurell \u003cMugurell@users.noreply.github.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2025743 - Avoid entering in edge to edge mode when QRFragment is shown  a=diannaS DONTBUILD\n\nQRFragment is part of Android Components and is not annotated with SystemInsetsPaddedFragment.\nWhen used in Fenix is is nested in a separate activity - QRScanActivity or inside of fragments\nlike PairFragment - which currently is annotated with SystemInsetsPaddedFragment.\nAs such it should be excluded from changing the edge-to-edge mode for HomeActivity.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D291397\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D292718\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/e2e/EdgeToEdgeFragmentLifecycleCallbacks.kt"], "git_node": "71ff21f4212d3c90cceb6987ee5dffec76e22c47", "git_parents": ["3e32101fc294b8a3fc881fce84a1e9a1b385b84b"], "node": "b8e4008f40348ccbc98cc1847612e85aabbf60f9", "parents": ["b55b7a4a82b568cc2756db0a696cc80e45d60cca"], "tags": []}], "date": 1775671446, "git_changesets": ["71ff21f4212d3c90cceb6987ee5dffec76e22c47"], "user": "dsmith@mozilla.com"}, "25605": {"changesets": [{"author": "iorgamgabriel \u003ciorgamgab